From 54cdaffbf03f058d2331efcb06e213f01fd9408a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Capivara CI <ci@capivara.dev>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 00:41:27 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] host: invoke the completion callback when an export-sync
 fence isn't found

EmulatedEglFenceSync with destroyWhenSignaled=true removes itself from
the handle registry as soon as it signals, via the render-control/pipe
channel. The GFXSTREAM_CREATE_EXPORT_SYNC virtio-gpu command that
leads to asyncWaitForGpuWithCb() arrives over a separate channel, with
no ordering guarantee relative to that signal+self-destruct -- a sync
that completes fast enough can vanish from the registry before this
lookup runs.

That's not an error, it means the wait is already satisfied. The
previous code logged it and silently dropped the completion callback,
leaving whoever's waiting on it (RanchuHwc's virtio-gpu timeline task,
and transitively the guest's DRM fence wait backing a composite/
present call) blocked forever -- a real Watchdog-tripping hang
confirmed live: RanchuHwc's binder thread stuck in
DrmVirtGpuResource::wait() -> dma_fence_default_wait, traced back to
exactly this dropped callback via a single "fence sync 0x... not
found" log line at the moment of the hang.

Same bug shape as the ASG host/guest lost-wakeup race (ring_stream.cpp,
0009): a cross-channel lifecycle race where "not found" should mean
"already done", not "silently drop and hang forever".
---
 host/frame_buffer.cpp | 15 ++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/host/frame_buffer.cpp b/host/frame_buffer.cpp
index 669138722..9422ff487 100644
--- a/host/frame_buffer.cpp
+++ b/host/frame_buffer.cpp
@@ -4972,7 +4972,20 @@ void FrameBuffer::Impl::asyncWaitForGpuWithCb(uint64_t eglsync, FenceCompletionC
     EmulatedEglFenceSync* fenceSync = EmulatedEglFenceSync::getFromHandle(eglsync);
 
     if (!fenceSync) {
-        GFXSTREAM_ERROR("err: fence sync 0x%llx not found", (unsigned long long)eglsync);
+        // EmulatedEglFenceSync with destroyWhenSignaled=true removes itself from the
+        // handle registry as soon as it signals (see decRef()/destroy()), via the
+        // render-control/pipe channel. The GFXSTREAM_CREATE_EXPORT_SYNC command that
+        // leads here arrives over the separate virtio-gpu command channel, with no
+        // ordering guarantee relative to that signal+self-destruct. A sync that
+        // signals fast enough can vanish from the registry before this lookup runs.
+        // That's not an error -- it means the wait is already satisfied -- so invoke
+        // the completion callback now instead of silently dropping it: dropping it
+        // leaves whoever's waiting on it (e.g. RanchuHwc's virtio-gpu timeline task,
+        // and transitively the guest's DRM fence wait backing a composite/present
+        // call) blocked forever.
+        GFXSTREAM_ERROR("fence sync 0x%llx not found, treating as already signaled",
+                         (unsigned long long)eglsync);
+        cb();
         return;
     }
 
